
Simplenote is a note taking application. The application works for the iPhone, iPad, Android, the internet, PC, Windows Phone, or Macintosh.[tpl]cite web |url = http://www.wired.com/gadgetlab/2010/08/hands-on-simplenote-3-stays-simple-gets-powerful|title = Hands-On: Simplenote 3 Stays Simple, Gets Powerful |first = Charlie |last = Sorrel |date = 24 August 2010 |work = Wired[/tpl] There is a premium version with extra features that includes syncing Simplenote with Dropbox.[tpl]cite web |url = http://www.macworld.com/appguide/app.html?id=89982&expand=false |title = Simplenote Review |first  = John |last = Fuller |work  = Macworld[/tpl] In addition, the Mac OS X program Notational Velocity can also sync with Simplenote.[tpl]cite web|url=http://lifehacker.com/5815743/the-best-syncing-note+taker-for-mac|last=Dachis|first=Adam|publisher=Lifehacker|accessdate=2012-01-11|date=2011-06-27|title=The Best Syncing Note-Taker for Mac[/tpl]. The application was reviewed by Mac Life,[tpl]cite web |url = http://www.maclife.com/article/features/app_showdown_simplenote_vs_notes_plus |title = App Showdown: Simplenote vs. Notes Plus |first = J |last = Keirn-Swanson |date = 22 December 2010 |work = Mac Life[/tpl] reviewed in the book Lifehacker: The Guide to Working Smarter, Faster, and Better,[tpl]cite web |url = http://books.google.com/books?id=d-FYJceblAMC&pg=PT146&dq=simplenote+application&hl=en&ei=MqdITrHVH8PhsQLG7_GRCA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=simplenote%20application&f=false |title = Lifehacker: The Guide to Working Smarter, Faster, and Better |first = Adam |last = Pash |coauthors = Trapani, Gina |year = 2011 |work = Lifehacker[/tpl] and covered in the book The Business of IPhone and IPad App Development''.[tpl]cite web |url = http://books.google.com/books?id=uF8Ccf80idkC&pg=PA220&dq=simplenote+application&hl=en&ei=MqdITrHVH8PhsQLG7_GRCA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCoQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=simplenote%20application&f=false |t